Description:
Solid Freestanding Two-bedroom Terrace in Prime Locale
A unique and rare opportunity now exists to buy into one of Collingwood's most sought-after pockets. Nestled next to semi-private parkland on one side, the home comprises two generous size bedrooms, (second with a north-facing aspect), lounge with adjacent dining and kitchen, full bathroom, a rear sunroom/study, established north/east back garden, original features boasting stained glass doors and decorative wall plaster mounts. Completely freestanding with wide side entrance, there is scope to renovate (STCA) with potential for conversion to full alfresco living at the rear. Close to main road arterials, several public transport options to the city, minutes to cafes, bars and any number of the unique cultural experiences that are Collingwood.
Insights: 20 Alexander Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Victorian grace, contemporary style: an elegant balcony terrace
This expansive tuck-pointed and pedimented 4BR residence, extended to combine period grace with light-filled style, is sure to impress! In a quiet street of quality homes, close to Smith and Brunswick Street cafes, parkland and schools (zoned Gold Street Primary), it offers a versatile floor plan comprising a handsome balcony bedroom plus three further double bedrooms; well-equipped kitchen (premium appliances and cabinetry) open to a spacious living room flowing through timber multifolds to a secluded al fresco entertaining courtyard; separate dining room, stylish bathroom (spa bath and shower) and powder room/laundry. Features of this immaculate home include polished jarrah floors, open fireplaces and other period detail, custom storage throughout and split-system air conditioning.

City-edge haven of designer style & seclusion
An inner urban, 2-level sanctuary of seclusion and serenity, this Boom-style Victorian is brilliantly renovated revealing classical elegance, contemporary style and a superbly landscaped alfresco oasis. Rising to a stunning retreat with views towards the city skyline, this private and peaceful terrace with double-glazed windows and doors delivers exceptional living and outdoor entertaining near all the excitement of Smith and Brunswick Streets, galleries, train station and parks. Description:
Attractive Brick Victorian with Original Frontage
Part of Collingwood's heritage walk, this 1860's workers cottage, steeped in history, sensitively renovated, exudes warmth and soul. Only minutes from Smith and Brunswick St precincts. The facade has been mindfully restored and is one of the few homes with intact, original frontage. This home is delightful as is or welcoming to the improvement or extension of a new generation. Gas heating, stove and cooktop. Pressed metal ceiling in front room. New roof, fuse box, water and gas lines.

Description:
Contemporary Style Personified
With muted neutral tones, clean lines and blend of luxury and industrial textures, this elegantly understated apartment by revered boutique developer Milieu sets the bar for the gold standard in contemporary style. With an uninterrupted view of the daily sunrise, the entire apartment boasts a captivating easterly aspect across the urban skyline out to the Dandenongs and comprises 2 bedrooms with BIRs, generously proportioned open plan living with living and meals zones, east facing balcony and well-appointed kitchen that features stainless steel bench tops/splashback with breakfast bar, integrated Smeg dishwasher cookware and soft closing drawers, integrated fridge, stone-and-tile lined bathroom, storage area with Euro laundry, ducted heating and cooling, double glazed windows, timber floors and exposed concrete ceilings. Architecturally crafted by renowned architects DKO, the impressive building (which has been shortlisted in the World Architecture Festival for Small Scale Housing) with its white-brick façade simultaneously strikes a distinct impression whilst finding unity with the urban fabric of historic Collingwood. Enjoying an enviable inner-city lifestyle, the apartment is closely located to an innumerable amount of popular restaurants, cafes and bars no further that its own street including Congress Wine & Espresso, Minanoie, The Plant Society and the Grace Darling Hotel just to name a few, not to mention vibrant Smith Street shops and trams at the end of the street and nearby Gertrude Street.
Insights: 305/47 Peel Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
A Stylish Modern Townhouse In Prime Location
The quality and detail are palpable the moment you enter this magnificent townhouse, beginning with a long gallery style hall and timber floors, leading to the master bedroom with full ensuite and open courtyard. Be further impressed when you ascend the stairs to the second-level of open-plan living, with a designer-built kitchen comprising stone benches, solid cabinetry and Smeg appliances, all blending effortlessly into more living spaces, including an alfresco balcony, a second bedroom and main bathroom. The top-level retreat boasts an attic-style roof with bar/kitchenette, views to the city, and a private east-facing balcony. Including garage and carport, reverse aircon. All in the idyllic locale of one Melbourne's most sought-after cultural pockets, with cafe, bar and artisan traders.
Note: No Body Corporate applies.

This handsome tuck-pointed residence, set back from the street on approximately 260 sq.m. land, offers secluded living within easy walking distance to Brunswick and Smith Street cafes, Queens Parade shops, CBD transport and easy access to the Eastern Freeway. Description:
Supreme Location, Enviable Apartment
Set in the highly sought Yorkshire Brewery development superbly located within Collingwood’s bustling coffee scene and surrounded by award winning restaurants on Smith Street & Brunswick Street, this attractive home sets itself apart with its unique features and superb size.
Upon entry you’re greeted with a generous open plan dining & lounge area that takes advantage of a North and South aspect. The kitchen is positioned as the focal point of the home and features a white stone benchtop, LED backdrop lighting, European Stainless-Steel appliances and soft close cupboards. Directly off the lounge a large full length sliding door invites you outside to a private terrace perfecting for entertaining friends and family. The hallway then invites you to the master bedroom with mirrored full length built in robes and a functional tiled bathroom.
Built to last, this energy conscious apartment also uses solar hot water, green energy switches, double glazing throughout and LED lighting throughout.
Adding to the desire of the Yorkshire Brewery, residents also have access to private facilities including roof top terrace and dining area, library, car share and bike share, dry cleaning, gymnasium, guest suites & an onsite Building Manager.
For an immediate inspection please contact Patrick on 0402 075 501.

Description:
Spectacular Views And Modern Living In Perfect Location
From Collingwood's prestigious and chic Yorkshire Brewery locale is one of the most excellent examples of city fringe living. This contemporary one-bedroom apartment has all the essentials plus a lot more. Including unobstructed views of the city skyline, and all the way to the Dandenong Ranges from the east-west covered balcony. Features include a stylish modern kitchen with gas cooktop, S/S appliances, stone benches and quality designer cabinetry. Extras include split system air conditioning, tiled bathroom, carpeted bedroom with mirrored robes, secure carpark and storage cage, 'FTTP Broadband', video intercom, double insulation, access to the communal rooftop BBQ and gymnasium. Situated so close to many of the hip bar and cafe treasures, with train and tram options to the city, the Eastern freeway and major arterials.
